{"ts":"2026-06-27T14:16:09.185Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"ozxl0bpx","input":{"summary":"Successfully connected the frontend SecureLogin UI to the Next.js App Router mock API backend authentication service (/api/v1/auth/login and /api/v1/auth/me) with full support for all user roles. \n\nSteps taken:\n1. Updated token storage synchronization by saving the JWT access token to both 'gff_ai_access_token' and 'gff_api_token' in localStorage upon successful authentication. This fixes a critical mismatch where apiClient requests (which look for 'gff_api_token') had missing authorization headers.\n2. Synchronized logout by updating 'clearPreviewSession' in 'lib/preview-auth.ts' to clean up 'gff_api_token', 'gff_ai_access_token', and the mock session object simultaneously.\n3. Enhanced the Next.js App Router API authentication backend ('lib/api-auth.ts') by mapping all remaining preview roles ('gff_operator', 'finance_admin', 'support_agent', 'viewer') to valid API mock users matching the credentials map of the SecureLogin component.\n4. Added TypeScript-safe role typing to 'ApiUser' to prevent strict union constraints on new roles.\n5. Ran full lint and compiler checks ('npx tsc --noEmit' and 'npm run lint') to guarantee perfect compilation, syntax correctness, and clean formatting. All validation tests passed cleanly without any errors.","verified":true}}}
